The essence of Badu, an innovative eco-hotel concept, lies in the quest for harmony with its environment, at the crossroads of sustainable tourism, hospitality and local authenticity. It offers an immersive experience in a world where nature merges with modern
comfort. Its brand identity embodies this perfect balance between nature and well-being. The warm, welcoming aspect of the experience is reflected in the hand-crafted typography of the logo.

As part of the Nikon Film Festival's on the theme of "fire", I took part in this short film, as assistant director, graphic designer and co-writer. Shot in sequence, the film follows two hooded robbers on their way to a heist who stop at a

traffic light (called ‘fire’ in French). The title and poster take up the film's retro universe and the gangster movies codes they play on, the better to accentuate the absurd discrepancy after viewing, without spoiling the comic spring or the film's only shot.
